{
  "article_id": "Gleason1950",
  "paragraphs": [
    [
      {
        "text": "San Nicolas",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "stands as the southern outpost of the "
      },
      {
        "text": "Channel Islands",
        "entity_key": "i_chi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", 53 miles off the nearest point of "
      },
      {
        "text": "the coast",
        "entity_key": "re_calcoast",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". Here the winds blow strong, scouring "
      },
      {
        "text": "this wasting island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "into grains of stinging sand, forming a long spit reaching out from the eastern end, south of which is the safest anchorage on "
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". "
      },
      {
        "text": "Eight miles long and but three in width, ",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "was once inhabited by ",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "a superior race of almost white Indians",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ],
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "(likely due to a sojourn of various trading ships).",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "The Russians",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ],
        "entity_keys": [
          "1814huntingparty",
          "rfurcompany",
          "iba"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "with their savage ",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Aleut hunters",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ],
        "entity_key": "natam_aleuts",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "in quest of sea otter found these women to their liking and killed the men who tried to defend them. By the time the otter were exterminated, only a small remnant of ",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the tribe",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ],
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "remained.",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "In 1835 "
      },
      {
        "text": "the Padres of the mission at Santa Barbara",
        "entity_keys": [
          "aji",
          "ndur",
          "misfats"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", thinking to save "
      },
      {
        "text": "the pagan souls",
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "on "
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", decided to remove them to "
      },
      {
        "text": "the mainland",
        "entity_key": "st_cal",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "An ambitious Mexican named "
      },
      {
        "text": "Joaquin Gomez",
        "entity_key": "jgo",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", had built "
      },
      {
        "text": "a little schooner",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "at "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara",
        "entity_key": "ci_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". He was evidently not too well pleased with the result of his labors, for he christened her "
      },
      {
        "text": "Peor es Nada",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": ", which freely translated means \"Better Than Nothing.\" Captained by "
      },
      {
        "text": "Charles Hubbard",
        "entity_key": "chu",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", "
      },
      {
        "text": "the vessel",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "sailed to "
      },
      {
        "text": "the tiny island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "and gathered up "
      },
      {
        "text": "the surviving inhabitants",
        "entity_key": "bhagroup",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ". A storm was coming on and "
      },
      {
        "text": "Captain Hubbard",
        "entity_key": "chu",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "made hurried preparations to leave, when "
      },
      {
        "text": "one of the women",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "found that "
      },
      {
        "text": "her babe",
        "entity_key": "lwchild",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "was not on board. "
      },
      {
        "text": "The safety of ",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the vessel",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ],
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "demanded an immediate departure but ",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the frantic mother",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "dove from the rail and swam for shore.",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "The "
      },
      {
        "text": "Peor es Nada",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "reached "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Pedro",
        "entity_key": "ci_sp",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "and "
      },
      {
        "text": "the Indians",
        "entity_key": "bhagroup",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "were distributed among the various missions while "
      },
      {
        "text": "the woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "on "
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "was all but forgotten. "
      },
      {
        "text": "Three attempts were made to find her during the next eighteen years and in 1853 ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "a number of men",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_keys": [
          "gni",
          "cdi",
          "col",
          "cook",
          "msh",
          "poli",
          "nsk",
          "hva"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "went over with ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Captain George Midevar [Nidever]",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", who combed the desolate wastes of ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". At last, under a shelter made of whalebone and brush, she was found, clad in a garment fashioned from bird skins and feathers.",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "By signs ",
        "tropes": [
          10
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the frightened woman",
        "tropes": [
          10
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "made it be known that ",
        "tropes": [
          10
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the baby",
        "tropes": [
          10
        ],
        "entity_key": "lwchild",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "had been killed by wild dogs.",
        "tropes": [
          10
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "She was taken to "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara",
        "entity_key": "ci_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "and christened "
      },
      {
        "text": "Juana Maria",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ". "
      },
      {
        "text": "Though she was given the best of care, she lived but six weeks, and ",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the last inhabitant of San Nicolas",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "was dead.",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Sheep were raised on "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicolas",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "at various times and during the great Los Angeles real estate boom of the '80s, town lots were laid out on "
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". It is now a "
      },
      {
        "text": "Naval Reserve",
        "entity_key": "re_pmugu",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "and is surrounded by restricted areas except for two short stretches of shoreline."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Aids to navigation consist of lights on the east end, north side, and south side about 2 1/2 miles from the eastern end. These beacons nightly send their cheering beams across the lonely waters."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Probably the most extensive abalone beds in the world are located here, due to the remoteness of "
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "and the restricted areas surrounding it."
      }
    ]
  ]
}